1
00:00:10,358 --> 00:00:13,697
I'm Mouri Kogoro. Private detective.

2
00:00:14,658 --> 00:00:18,040
Yes... my trade is digging up people's dirt.

3
00:00:18,499 --> 00:00:21,213
To soothe a heart sickened
by such work...

4
00:00:21,296 --> 00:00:26,056
Most detectives keep
a secret bar of their own.

5
00:00:26,139 --> 00:00:27,308
Alright!

6
00:00:27,392 --> 00:00:29,396
Young people shouting and whooping...

7
00:00:29,479 --> 00:00:32,068
Having their fun with billiards and darts.
This place...

8
00:00:32,318 --> 00:00:35,449
Is, regrettably,
not my bar, but...

9
00:00:35,533 --> 00:00:39,082
When the client is the bartender here,
what can you do?

10
00:00:40,501 --> 00:00:44,259
Here you go, Detective.
For now, please have this.

11
00:00:44,551 --> 00:00:47,890
Her name is
Fukui Yuzuki, 26 years old.

12
00:00:47,975 --> 00:00:49,769
The bartender
at this establishment.

13
00:00:50,479 --> 00:00:53,068
She's probably
in love with me.

14
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:56,575
The proof of that is
this pale green cocktail...

15
00:00:56,658 --> 00:00:59,831
She's treating me
to a gimlet.

16
00:01:01,752 --> 00:01:03,547
She must see me
as that detective...

17
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:06,178
Philip Marlowe.
No doubt about it.

18
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:07,722
Hm...

19
00:01:08,724 --> 00:01:10,979
Hey, this is green tea!

20
00:01:11,062 --> 00:01:14,068
Sorry... I figured if you got drunk
you couldn't do your job.

21
00:01:14,152 --> 00:01:15,154
Ah, right...

22
00:01:15,863 --> 00:01:18,160
Well, hold on, hold on. From the top.

23
00:01:18,995 --> 00:01:22,001
I'm Mouri Kogoro. Private detective.

24
00:01:22,376 --> 00:01:26,259
This is a pool bar where the client
works as the bartender.

25
00:01:26,635 --> 00:01:28,388
What soothes my soul...

26
00:01:28,472 --> 00:01:31,561
Is the offbeat jazz rhythm
flowing through this place...

27
00:01:31,645 --> 00:01:33,315
Hey! Old man!

28
00:01:33,398 --> 00:01:34,944
A brat's voice.

29
00:01:35,361 --> 00:01:36,363
Huh?

30
00:01:37,698 --> 00:01:40,579
Huh... Wait, what are you
doing here?!

31
00:01:40,663 --> 00:01:41,832
Well, Ran-neechan said...

32
00:01:41,915 --> 00:01:45,548
Dinner's getting cold,
so hurry up and bring him back.

33
00:01:45,631 --> 00:01:48,262
I told you I'm here for work!

34
00:01:48,345 --> 00:01:52,061
And I told her, you probably just said that
so you could come drink.

35
00:01:52,687 --> 00:01:55,150
It is for work, right? A tough case?

36
00:01:55,234 --> 00:01:56,653
Uh... Yes.

37
00:01:56,736 --> 00:01:57,780
See? Told you.

38
00:01:57,864 --> 00:01:58,992
What kind of case?

39
00:01:59,617 --> 00:02:01,998
There's this strange sound
while I'm working.

40
00:02:02,331 --> 00:02:05,922
A "pop"... like the sound
of uncorking a champagne bottle.

41
00:02:06,548 --> 00:02:10,806
The sound of uncorking
a champagne bottle?

42
00:02:11,308 --> 00:02:17,320
♪~

43
00:02:24,334 --> 00:02:27,882
Black shadows and pitch-black darkness...
The light of deduction cuts right through.

44
00:02:27,966 --> 00:02:31,723
Pool Bar "Blue Parrot"...
Where drinks invite disaster.

45
00:02:31,806 --> 00:02:33,435
Seeing through the one and only truth...

46
00:02:33,518 --> 00:02:35,147
A child's appearance, an adult's mind...

47
00:02:35,481 --> 00:02:38,236
His name is Detective Conan!

48
00:04:00,025 --> 00:04:06,037
~♪

49
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:15,820
"Kogoro is at the Bar (Part 1)"

50
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:18,600
Ah!
Whoa, whoa...

51
00:04:18,754 --> 00:04:20,340
See? That sound.

52
00:04:20,966 --> 00:04:25,016
Well, that was literally
the sound of uncorking champagne...

53
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:29,901
But at that time, we weren't serving
any champagne to customers...

54
00:04:30,276 --> 00:04:33,658
Couldn't a customer have
snuck some in?

55
00:04:34,034 --> 00:04:36,288
Wine bottles have corks too.

56
00:04:36,372 --> 00:04:38,167
I thought the same thing...

57
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:41,048
So I kept a close eye
on the customers, but...

58
00:04:41,507 --> 00:04:45,056
Nobody was drinking
champagne or wine...

59
00:04:45,139 --> 00:04:48,939
And after the sound,
I also heard something like something falling...

60
00:04:49,523 --> 00:04:52,112
I looked around while cleaning
after closing, but...

61
00:04:52,195 --> 00:04:54,742
No cork had fallen anywhere.

62
00:04:55,410 --> 00:04:57,790
But there was a strange smell...

63
00:04:58,124 --> 00:05:00,336
A strange smell?
Hm?

64
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:03,592
Don't tell me... the smell of gunpowder
from some kind of explosion?

65
00:05:03,676 --> 00:05:06,891
Oh, no... It was like
the scent of yuzu.

66
00:05:06,975 --> 00:05:09,731
Just a faint whiff of it, though.

67
00:05:09,981 --> 00:05:12,778
Since my name has "Yuzu" in it...

68
00:05:12,862 --> 00:05:15,408
I've always been sensitive
to the smell of yuzu.

69
00:05:15,909 --> 00:05:19,709
We don't use yuzu in this bar,
so I thought it was strange...

70
00:05:19,792 --> 00:05:22,422
And that's why I consulted Mouri-san.

71
00:05:22,422 --> 00:05:27,200
Couldn't a customer have spilled
a cocktail that uses a similar citrus?

72
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:30,520
Like, a gimlet uses lime juice...

73
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:33,720
Or a screwdriver,
or a white lady...

74
00:05:34,820 --> 00:05:37,720
Hmm... I really thought
it smelled like yuzu, though.

75
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:40,120
That sound... it happened more than once?

76
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:43,120
Yes. 2 or 3 times on different days.

77
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:47,020
Was there a customer who was always here
when the sound happened?

78
00:05:47,020 --> 00:05:50,720
There is. As it happens,
right now at the table behind us...

79
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:53,220
That group of four.
They're the ones.

80
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:55,420
Alright, I'm taking the shot!

81
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:57,320
Okay, cheese!

82
00:05:58,820 --> 00:06:01,720
Ah, Chief! The film's run out!
- Kogure Monpei (28), employee.

83
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,620
It's fine, it's fine.

84
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:06,720
I've got two or three spare film rolls stocked up myself too.
- Usuda Chikafumi (51), department manager.

85
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:10,220
And I had them stock up on plenty more so we're good.

86
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:14,020
Right?
Ah... Yes.

87
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:16,220
Here, Kogure-kun.
Ah...

88
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:21,420
But Chief... An analog camera these days... Isn't that just a hassle?
- Hatsumura Kensaku (31), employee.

89
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,184
Hmph. I hate digital.

90
00:06:24,210 --> 00:06:24,843
(hiccup)

91
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:29,020
Remember... (hiccup) there was one guy in our department too, wasn't there?

92
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:30,520
All smug about how
he was a digital whiz...

93
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:33,720
A useless geek.

94
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,820
You mean Yoshikuwa-kun?

95
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:37,820
Yeah, Yoshikuwa. Yoshikuwa.

96
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:39,520
When you dive that deep
into digital like that guy...

97
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:41,520
You lose touch with reality, become a shut-in... (hiccup) ..

98
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:48,951
And in the end you go and hang yourself.... (hiccup)

99
00:06:49,420 --> 00:06:54,720
Oh, that reminds me... Kishiura-kun...
I heard you and that guy were pretty close?

100
00:06:54,774 --> 00:06:56,736
If you're lonely without a boyfriend...
- Kishiura Mika (30), employee.

101
00:06:56,819 --> 00:06:59,658
I wouldn't mind
keeping you company.

102
00:06:59,742 --> 00:07:02,247
Oh, no... I'll pass.

103
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:05,169
What? No need to be shy.

104
00:07:05,253 --> 00:07:07,090
Considering how close we are...

105
00:07:07,173 --> 00:07:08,175
Hey, Chief!

106
00:07:08,259 --> 00:07:10,680
Hm? What is it, Hatsumura?

107
00:07:11,223 --> 00:07:14,814
I bought that billiard cue
you asked for.

108
00:07:14,897 --> 00:07:19,406
A top-of-the-line ebony model
was on sale at a discount, so...

109
00:07:19,489 --> 00:07:23,163
Oh, really? Thanks, Hatsumura-kun.

110
00:07:23,247 --> 00:07:25,626
It's the best gift ever.

111
00:07:25,711 --> 00:07:27,171
Oh, a gift?

112
00:07:27,881 --> 00:07:31,723
This is my birthday present,
right?

113
00:07:31,806 --> 00:07:33,684
Huh? Uh... Yeah.

114
00:07:34,311 --> 00:07:37,650
I brought these too.
Your personal darts, Chief.

115
00:07:37,735 --> 00:07:40,406
Soft darts with plastic tips
are pretty common...

116
00:07:40,489 --> 00:07:42,410
But tracking down
these metal hard darts...

117
00:07:42,493 --> 00:07:45,374
Was a real pain.

118
00:07:45,458 --> 00:07:46,919
Is that so? Good, good.

119
00:07:47,003 --> 00:07:48,339
You two really are useful.

120
00:07:49,049 --> 00:07:56,620
O-Of course... I was planning
to give these as a present too.

121
00:07:56,620 --> 00:08:02,020
Kogure, do you know why I wanted the steel darts?

122
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:03,520
N-No...

123
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:05,620
It's because...

124
00:08:08,071 --> 00:08:10,115
Ah... Ahh!

125
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:15,420
See? You can't scare someone
like that with plastic ones.

126
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:19,400
Hahahaha! Ahahaha...

127
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:23,520
Oh, looks like the billiard table
just opened up.

128
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:27,620
Since you went out of your way to get the cue for me,

129
00:08:27,620 --> 00:08:29,720
I guess I may as well try it out!

130
00:08:30,894 --> 00:08:32,012
(clears throat)

131
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:35,974
Ah... Anyway! Just go home already and tell Ran this:

132
00:08:36,268 --> 00:08:39,607
Kogoro-san has taken on
a very difficult case...

133
00:08:39,691 --> 00:08:42,363
And won't be home for a while.

134
00:08:42,447 --> 00:08:46,079
...And with that settled, Yuzuki-chan,
fix me a gimlet, would you?

135
00:08:46,163 --> 00:08:49,210
Uh... Can you really work
if you're drinking?

136
00:08:49,544 --> 00:08:51,924
It's fine, it's fine.

137
00:08:52,175 --> 00:08:55,014
Don't come crying to me later.

138
00:08:59,272 --> 00:09:03,030
Hey, old man... Let's just go home.

139
00:09:03,113 --> 00:09:05,075
Ran-neechan was furious.

140
00:09:05,159 --> 00:09:07,873
...Geez, you're annoying.
How many times are you gonna come back?

141
00:09:08,332 --> 00:09:10,669
I told you, I'm working!

142
00:09:11,046 --> 00:09:13,175
You're just drinking.

143
00:09:13,258 --> 00:09:17,266
Ugh... Yuzuki-chan,
one more gimlet.

144
00:09:17,350 --> 00:09:20,732
Come on, please think about the case!

145
00:09:20,815 --> 00:09:24,155
Once this mystery's solved,
I want to post about it on my blog!

146
00:09:24,239 --> 00:09:28,372
Heh... No worries.
I've pretty much solved it already.

147
00:09:28,455 --> 00:09:30,000
Huh? Really?

148
00:09:30,417 --> 00:09:31,419
Seriously?

149
00:09:32,338 --> 00:09:35,845
The culprit probably
spilled some ponzu.

150
00:09:35,929 --> 00:09:37,640
With yuzu in it, no less.

151
00:09:37,891 --> 00:09:40,312
Hm... Ponzu with yuzu?

152
00:09:40,396 --> 00:09:41,481
Hey...

153
00:09:42,024 --> 00:09:43,861
Which means, in other words...

154
00:09:44,905 --> 00:09:45,907
In other words?

155
00:09:47,911 --> 00:09:50,374
In other words, yuzu go "pop."

156
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:53,589
Yuzu went pop!
Just kidding!

157
00:09:53,672 --> 00:09:56,177
Bahahaha...

158
00:09:56,595 --> 00:09:58,223
This old man is hopeless.

159
00:09:58,975 --> 00:10:01,731
Ahahaha... Hehehe...

160
00:10:03,442 --> 00:10:06,448
In the end, the chief
passed out, huh?

161
00:10:06,531 --> 00:10:10,915
Yeah... He can't hold his liquor
but always wants to drink.

162
00:10:10,999 --> 00:10:12,376
More importantly, my wallet hurts.

163
00:10:13,003 --> 00:10:16,761
That billiard cue
cost 100,000 yen.

164
00:10:17,094 --> 00:10:21,269
And the darts I bought,
with the case, were 60,000.

165
00:10:21,353 --> 00:10:25,235
Kishiura's lucky...
Just five or six rolls of camera film, right?

166
00:10:25,486 --> 00:10:27,114
I told you...

167
00:10:27,198 --> 00:10:29,410
Because it was his birthday,
he made me buy an idol poster...

168
00:10:29,494 --> 00:10:32,124
Off an online auction.

169
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:35,005
Oh yeah, you gave it to him at the office.

170
00:10:35,089 --> 00:10:37,510
It was autographed,
so it cost 30,000 yen.

171
00:10:37,761 --> 00:10:39,639
Can I take a quick look?

172
00:10:39,723 --> 00:10:43,355
Don't get it dirty.
I'll get yelled at by the chief.

173
00:10:43,647 --> 00:10:47,864
I know, I know.
Oh wow, it's Okino Yoko!

174
00:10:48,448 --> 00:10:51,789
So, before we head home,
want to grab another drink?

175
00:10:51,872 --> 00:10:52,874
Sure.

176
00:10:53,417 --> 00:10:57,007
Hey, you've just been making
highballs all night. You've barely had any, right?

177
00:10:57,091 --> 00:10:58,385
Hmm... Now that you mention it.

178
00:10:59,303 --> 00:11:02,685
Seems like you were just
crushing ice with that thing the whole time.

179
00:11:02,936 --> 00:11:05,775
So how about that champagne
we had at the start?

180
00:11:05,859 --> 00:11:08,280
Yeah, that was good stuff.

181
00:11:08,363 --> 00:11:09,365
What do you think?

182
00:11:09,449 --> 00:11:11,035
Sounds good.

183
00:11:11,119 --> 00:11:14,041
Excuse me... A bottle of champagne.

184
00:11:14,125 --> 00:11:16,922
Right away.
And three glasses.

185
00:11:17,006 --> 00:11:20,637
Hey... That guy at the counter...
Isn't that Mouri Kogoro?

186
00:11:20,972 --> 00:11:23,351
What? No way...
The famous detective?

187
00:11:23,435 --> 00:11:27,401
Hm? I feel like
I'm being watched...

188
00:11:27,485 --> 00:11:28,946
Get a photo, get a photo!

189
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:30,574
Just some lookalike, right?

190
00:11:30,657 --> 00:11:33,706
Yeah... Can't be
a drunk like that.

191
00:11:33,998 --> 00:11:35,501
Hahaha...

192
00:11:36,336 --> 00:11:37,964
(straining sounds)

193
00:11:38,048 --> 00:11:41,346
I'm really no good
at this kind of thing.

194
00:11:41,429 --> 00:11:43,810
Hey, hey... Don't point that at me.

195
00:11:43,893 --> 00:11:46,899
Ugh... Kogure-kun, please.

196
00:11:47,399 --> 00:11:49,947
When it comes to brute strength,
Kogure's the man.

197
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:52,034
Yeah, yeah... Leave it to me.

198
00:11:52,117 --> 00:11:53,203
(straining sounds)

199
00:11:53,286 --> 00:11:57,586
Huh? What the...
This thing is seriously stuck.

200
00:11:57,670 --> 00:12:00,342
Hey, don't let it spray over here!

201
00:12:00,425 --> 00:12:01,971
I know, I know!

202
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:04,517
(straining sounds)

203
00:12:07,356 --> 00:12:08,692
Ah! It's spraying!

204
00:12:08,776 --> 00:12:11,782
You idiot... It got on the poster!

205
00:12:11,866 --> 00:12:13,870
That really was the sound
I've been hearing...

206
00:12:13,953 --> 00:12:16,249
That was champagne too, right?

207
00:12:16,499 --> 00:12:18,545
The edge of the poster's all wet!

208
00:12:18,628 --> 00:12:19,840
Th-This is bad...

209
00:12:19,923 --> 00:12:23,263
Ah... Sorry...
Three hand towels, please.

210
00:12:23,346 --> 00:12:24,640
Right away.

211
00:12:32,782 --> 00:12:35,914
What about that sound just now?
The hand towel wrapper opening?

212
00:12:36,331 --> 00:12:38,836
Is it different from the sound
you heard, miss?

213
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:40,172
Yeah...

214
00:12:40,547 --> 00:12:45,098
I think that cork popping sound
from before was closer.

215
00:12:48,104 --> 00:12:50,692
Hey, some of it got
on the chief, too!

216
00:12:50,777 --> 00:12:53,741
Whoa, crap... Hm? What?

217
00:12:54,158 --> 00:12:57,373
There's a red dot or something
on the chief's neck.

218
00:12:57,456 --> 00:12:58,751
You're right.

219
00:12:58,834 --> 00:13:02,383
Wait, more like...
Th-The chief isn't breathing...

220
00:13:02,926 --> 00:13:05,097
N-No way...

221
00:13:05,180 --> 00:13:08,311
Huh? Chief? Chief?!

222
00:13:08,395 --> 00:13:09,397
Ah!

223
00:13:12,904 --> 00:13:15,283
Huh? Chief!
Huh?!

224
00:13:15,367 --> 00:13:16,577
Are you okay?!

225
00:13:17,121 --> 00:13:18,708
Hey, what's wrong?!

226
00:13:18,791 --> 00:13:21,714
Th-The chief...
He won't wake up. He looks dead!

227
00:13:21,797 --> 00:13:23,258
What?!

228
00:13:25,470 --> 00:13:28,268
No... Not "looks dead."

229
00:13:28,769 --> 00:13:31,524
This one really is dead.

230
00:13:44,430 --> 00:13:47,519
I'm Mouri Kogoro. Private detective.

231
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:52,446
I took a case from Fukui Yuzuki-chan,
the bartender who's in love with me...

232
00:13:52,529 --> 00:13:55,577
And came to the pool bar
where she works, but...

233
00:13:56,077 --> 00:13:59,794
As it turns out, the one
with an obsession for me...

234
00:14:00,044 --> 00:14:02,674
Seems to be trouble itself.

235
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:06,306
We can't say for certain
without an autopsy, but...

236
00:14:07,099 --> 00:14:10,607
The cause of death is likely
asphyxiation due to a neurotoxin.

237
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:12,235
P-Poisoned?!

238
00:14:12,444 --> 00:14:15,492
Yes. From the wound at the back of his neck,

239
00:14:16,076 --> 00:14:20,292
it seems he was stabbed with something sharp like an awl, that had been coated with poison.

240
00:14:20,376 --> 00:14:22,548
But if someone stabbed him with that...

241
00:14:22,631 --> 00:14:25,302
He'd have thrashed around and screamed.

242
00:14:25,386 --> 00:14:27,683
I believe he died in his sleep.

243
00:14:28,202 --> 00:14:28,874
Huh?

244
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:32,400
The victim appears to have died while drunk.

245
00:14:32,484 --> 00:14:34,446
...Wait. You again?

246
00:14:34,530 --> 00:14:36,366
Yes, Inspector.

247
00:14:36,826 --> 00:14:40,082
Don't tell me you just happened to be at another murder scene again?

248
00:14:40,165 --> 00:14:43,130
Well, yeah... I just happened to be here.

249
00:14:43,631 --> 00:14:46,554
Indeed... A detective has
a duty of confidentiality.

250
00:14:46,637 --> 00:14:50,562
No matter what happens, he must never tell others about his clients.

251
00:14:51,271 --> 00:14:54,612
To ensure no suspicion falls upon Yuzuki-chan...

252
00:14:54,695 --> 00:14:56,824
I shall keep my lips sealed about my client.

253
00:14:57,199 --> 00:14:58,995
On my pride as a detective.

254
00:14:59,078 --> 00:15:00,832
I'm the one who called him here.

255
00:15:00,916 --> 00:15:02,043
What?!

256
00:15:02,628 --> 00:15:04,757
There's a mystery
I wanted Mouri-san to solve.

257
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,842
A mystery?

258
00:15:06,134 --> 00:15:09,223
While I'm working,
there's this popping sound.

259
00:15:09,307 --> 00:15:11,687
Like the sound of uncorking
a champagne bottle.

260
00:15:11,979 --> 00:15:13,023
Huh?

261
00:15:13,106 --> 00:15:14,860
Of course, at those times...

262
00:15:14,944 --> 00:15:17,658
We weren't serving champagne
to any customers...

263
00:15:17,741 --> 00:15:19,453
And even after cleaning up
after closing...

264
00:15:19,536 --> 00:15:22,918
We never found anything
like a cork.

265
00:15:23,001 --> 00:15:25,882
Just a faint
yuzu-like scent.

266
00:15:26,216 --> 00:15:28,721
By the way, how much
did you take this case for?

267
00:15:29,305 --> 00:15:32,269
She said she'd wipe my tab clean.

268
00:15:32,353 --> 00:15:34,858
But of course, I do intend
to properly pay...

269
00:15:34,942 --> 00:15:36,862
For the gimlets I had tonight.

270
00:15:36,946 --> 00:15:38,240
Huh? R-Really?

271
00:15:38,741 --> 00:15:42,833
So? The people drinking
with the victim...

272
00:15:42,916 --> 00:15:45,463
Those three, correct?

273
00:15:45,547 --> 00:15:46,549
Yes.

274
00:15:46,966 --> 00:15:51,266
I asked them a few things
before you arrived, Inspector.

275
00:15:51,767 --> 00:15:56,067
From the right:
Kishiura Mika-san, 30 years old.

276
00:15:56,485 --> 00:15:59,323
Hatsumura Kensaku-san, 31 years old.

277
00:15:59,783 --> 00:16:02,581
Kogure Monpei-san, 28 years old.

278
00:16:03,541 --> 00:16:07,507
All three work at the same company
as the murdered Usuda-san...

279
00:16:07,591 --> 00:16:10,680
And tonight they were celebrating
his birthday here...

280
00:16:10,764 --> 00:16:12,809
Since he was their department chief.

281
00:16:12,893 --> 00:16:14,103
I see.

282
00:16:14,813 --> 00:16:17,944
So one of these three...

283
00:16:18,028 --> 00:16:22,244
Held a grudge against their boss
and poisoned him.

284
00:16:22,328 --> 00:16:24,373
H-Hold on a minute.

285
00:16:24,458 --> 00:16:27,714
We just came here to celebrate his birthday...

286
00:16:27,798 --> 00:16:29,551
We didn't poison anyone!

287
00:16:30,512 --> 00:16:32,891
Couldn't the three of you
have done it together?

288
00:16:32,974 --> 00:16:34,478
You kept glancing at me,
the detective...

289
00:16:34,937 --> 00:16:37,233
And whispering to each other.

290
00:16:37,316 --> 00:16:38,653
That was about you...

291
00:16:38,736 --> 00:16:41,366
We were saying you looked
like "Sleeping Kogoro."

292
00:16:41,617 --> 00:16:43,496
Didn't think it was really you.

293
00:16:43,579 --> 00:16:46,877
Besides, we don't even have a motive.

294
00:16:46,961 --> 00:16:48,338
But, I mean...

295
00:16:48,422 --> 00:16:52,806
After the chief passed out drunk,
you three were talking, right?

296
00:16:52,889 --> 00:16:56,772
About how you were forced to buy
super expensive birthday presents...

297
00:16:56,856 --> 00:16:58,275
And how mad you were about it.

298
00:16:59,026 --> 00:17:01,281
Y-You were listening, kid?

299
00:17:01,364 --> 00:17:03,536
Yeah... I've got good ears.

300
00:17:03,619 --> 00:17:06,124
Also, about how the chief
was making fun of that guy...

301
00:17:06,207 --> 00:17:08,671
Yoshikuwa-san, and how
he committed suicide...

302
00:17:09,088 --> 00:17:13,556
And how you and that Yoshikuwa-san
were lovers.

303
00:17:14,474 --> 00:17:15,560
Is that true?

304
00:17:16,394 --> 00:17:18,148
Yeah... It is.

305
00:17:18,231 --> 00:17:22,281
But if you're saying that,
Hatsumura-san was his senpai in college...

306
00:17:22,364 --> 00:17:24,745
And Kogure-kun joined the company
the same year he did.

307
00:17:24,828 --> 00:17:28,084
Besides, if we hated someone
enough to kill them...

308
00:17:28,168 --> 00:17:30,465
We wouldn't play billiards
or darts with them.

309
00:17:30,924 --> 00:17:32,552
You played games with the victim?

310
00:17:32,844 --> 00:17:37,562
Yeah. The three of us
took turns playing him...

311
00:17:38,648 --> 00:17:42,739
Hey, did the chief really
play with those three?

312
00:17:42,822 --> 00:17:43,908
Ah... Right.

313
00:17:43,991 --> 00:17:47,081
You kept going home,
so you didn't see, Conan-kun.

314
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:50,254
The chief was a real handful.

315
00:17:50,337 --> 00:17:53,176
The dartboard here
is for soft darts...

316
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:55,974
But he tried to use
the hard darts he'd been given...

317
00:17:56,057 --> 00:17:58,604
So he got into it
with the other customers.

318
00:17:59,146 --> 00:18:02,487
Those three stepped in
and managed to calm things down...

319
00:18:03,656 --> 00:18:05,702
And until the chief sobered up...

320
00:18:05,785 --> 00:18:08,164
They seemed to be letting him
rest at the table.

321
00:18:08,248 --> 00:18:09,793
So what about after that?

322
00:18:09,876 --> 00:18:13,091
For a while, the three of them
were playing billiards and darts.

323
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:16,097
Like, the loser swaps out.

324
00:18:16,557 --> 00:18:19,771
So when two of them
were playing...

325
00:18:19,855 --> 00:18:23,529
The remaining one was alone
with the drunk chief.

326
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:28,914
In other words, each of you three
had an opportunity...

327
00:18:28,998 --> 00:18:30,918
To be alone with the chief.

328
00:18:31,754 --> 00:18:35,970
Anyway, we'll be conducting
a body check and searching your belongings.

329
00:18:38,726 --> 00:18:41,690
Hmm. A billiard cue, huh?

330
00:18:42,107 --> 00:18:44,278
Certainly looks expensive.

331
00:18:44,362 --> 00:18:47,117
Yeah... A 160,000 yen item...

332
00:18:47,201 --> 00:18:49,664
Was on sale for 100,000,
so I got it for the chief.

333
00:18:50,207 --> 00:18:54,340
O-Of course... Like the kid heard,
I never planned...

334
00:18:54,424 --> 00:18:57,137
On giving such an expensive present...

335
00:18:57,221 --> 00:18:59,141
So I was a bit annoyed.

336
00:18:59,518 --> 00:19:02,314
But do you really think
I'd commit murder over that?

337
00:19:02,398 --> 00:19:03,859
But...
Huh?

338
00:19:04,235 --> 00:19:06,990
If you attached a poison needle
to the tip of this cue...

339
00:19:07,074 --> 00:19:10,832
You could stab him from a distance,
even away from the table.

340
00:19:10,915 --> 00:19:11,917
What?!

341
00:19:12,334 --> 00:19:15,842
Something that conspicuous...
Someone would remember it.

342
00:19:15,925 --> 00:19:17,846
Right? I didn't do
anything like that.

343
00:19:17,929 --> 00:19:18,931
No.

344
00:19:19,599 --> 00:19:23,941
Once the chief passed out,
he put it back in its case right away.

345
00:19:24,818 --> 00:19:27,449
I see. And this?

346
00:19:27,907 --> 00:19:31,289
The darts that caused
the trouble with the other customers...

347
00:19:31,372 --> 00:19:34,754
I didn't buy those on purpose
to cause trouble!

348
00:19:34,838 --> 00:19:37,802
The chief told me
to buy hard darts...

349
00:19:38,679 --> 00:19:42,352
I got an antique dartboard
that belonged to my grandfather...

350
00:19:42,437 --> 00:19:45,902
And when I gave it to the chief,
he told me to buy darts for it...

351
00:19:45,985 --> 00:19:48,741
I don't play darts
at all myself...

352
00:19:49,241 --> 00:19:52,164
That reminds me... The chief
pretended to throw a dart at you...

353
00:19:52,247 --> 00:19:53,918
You were pretty terrified.

354
00:19:54,001 --> 00:19:56,047
Ah... Ahh!

355
00:19:56,339 --> 00:19:59,888
Yeah, that seriously
freaked me out...

356
00:19:59,971 --> 00:20:02,936
So couldn't you have coated the tip
with poison and thrown it from a distance...

357
00:20:03,394 --> 00:20:05,190
And just stabbed him?

358
00:20:05,273 --> 00:20:08,572
I told you,
I'm terrible at darts.

359
00:20:08,656 --> 00:20:10,785
Besides, rather than
throwing from far away...

360
00:20:10,868 --> 00:20:13,624
It'd be way easier and more reliable
to just stab him up close.

361
00:20:13,707 --> 00:20:15,252
Well, that's true...

362
00:20:15,335 --> 00:20:17,840
If you suspect me,
then just check them!

363
00:20:17,924 --> 00:20:19,719
Go over those dart tips
thoroughly.

364
00:20:20,262 --> 00:20:22,976
Of course, I intend to.

365
00:20:23,811 --> 00:20:26,692
And you... A few rolls
of camera film...

366
00:20:26,775 --> 00:20:28,737
And an idol poster?

367
00:20:29,029 --> 00:20:32,160
Rather cheap compared
to the other two.

368
00:20:32,244 --> 00:20:36,252
Hey, that poster was autographed...
It cost 30,000 yen!

369
00:20:36,712 --> 00:20:38,674
Well, he kept saying he wanted it...

370
00:20:38,757 --> 00:20:41,304
Over and over, right next to my desk...

371
00:20:41,387 --> 00:20:43,559
So I didn't have much choice
but to buy it.

372
00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:44,644
Ah...

373
00:20:45,270 --> 00:20:49,320
Hm? This wet spot
on the poster... It smells.

374
00:20:49,904 --> 00:20:52,367
This scent... Is it yuzu?

375
00:20:53,829 --> 00:20:55,373
Th-This is...

376
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:56,793
So the old man noticed too.

377
00:20:56,877 --> 00:20:58,964
It's a poster
of Yoko-chan!

378
00:20:59,048 --> 00:21:02,220
And what's more, the legendary
Western bikini shot!

379
00:21:02,304 --> 00:21:03,306
That's your takeaway?!

380
00:21:03,389 --> 00:21:07,482
...And don't get it wet!
A beautiful woman, all soaked!

381
00:21:07,565 --> 00:21:08,817
And a pun... really?

382
00:21:09,109 --> 00:21:13,201
When Kogure-kun uncorked the champagne,
it sprayed everywhere.

383
00:21:14,119 --> 00:21:18,294
More importantly...
You took quite a lot of photos, didn't you?

384
00:21:18,378 --> 00:21:20,675
Did your boss like taking photos?

385
00:21:21,050 --> 00:21:24,599
Yeah he liked taking them for his blog.

386
00:21:24,683 --> 00:21:27,647
Though the ones picking the photos and uploading them

387
00:21:27,730 --> 00:21:29,149
Were us.

388
00:21:29,233 --> 00:21:31,613
The chief was digitally illiterate.

389
00:21:31,697 --> 00:21:35,036
Yet he wanted to seem cool by having a blog...

390
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:38,585
Well I guess at least after everything that's happened we won't have to pick out photos.

391
00:21:38,669 --> 00:21:40,589
It was a blessing in disguise.

392
00:21:40,673 --> 00:21:44,304
Ah... B-But we wouldn't
commit murder over hating that, okay?

393
00:21:44,388 --> 00:21:45,390
Ahah...

394
00:21:45,474 --> 00:21:49,356
By the way, who was in charge of mixing up and diluting the whiskey?

395
00:21:49,441 --> 00:21:52,447
That was mostly me...

396
00:21:52,905 --> 00:21:55,911
Then I'll have this
checked out as well.

397
00:21:55,995 --> 00:22:00,003
The ice pick is sharp and pointed too, just like the tips of the darts.

398
00:22:00,086 --> 00:22:03,342
It's very close to the shape of the murder weapon.

399
00:22:09,104 --> 00:22:12,110
I'm Mouri Kogoro. Private detective.

400
00:22:12,820 --> 00:22:16,076
It seems my very nature
as a detective...

401
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:18,707
Has brought calamity to this pool bar...

402
00:22:18,791 --> 00:22:21,128
Which should have been
a place of solace.

403
00:22:22,465 --> 00:22:23,634
Good grief.

404
00:22:24,218 --> 00:22:25,971
It seems tonight as well...

405
00:22:26,055 --> 00:22:29,186
This case won't let me sleep.

406
00:22:32,067 --> 00:22:38,079
♪~

407
00:23:46,424 --> 00:23:51,685
~♪

408
00:23:52,185 --> 00:23:55,316
No traces of poison
were found?!

409
00:23:55,985 --> 00:23:58,991
...Geez. No murder weapon...

410
00:23:59,074 --> 00:24:01,871
It's just like that pickpocket case
the other day.

411
00:24:02,832 --> 00:24:05,671
Hm? This is...

412
00:24:06,464 --> 00:24:09,971
Why is there clay
on the bottom of that thing...

413
00:24:10,221 --> 00:24:13,729
Then the culprit is, after all,
the customer who fought with the victim?

414
00:24:14,312 --> 00:24:15,774
No way...

415
00:24:16,013 --> 00:24:21,413
Next Conan:
"Kogoro is at the Bar (Part 2)"

416
00:24:37,213 --> 00:24:39,613
Next Conan's Hint:

417
00:24:39,613 --> 00:24:41,613
"Clay"

418
00:24:41,741 --> 00:24:43,035
There's no clay
in a bar.

419
00:24:43,118 --> 00:24:44,413
Mouri-kun...
Are you drunk?

420
00:24:44,496 --> 00:24:46,584
Old man, you're fine
staying at the bar forever.
